headline: Warren Buffett Will Make Over $1.33 Billion This Year From Investing in These 2 High-Yielding Dividend Stocks
summary: Warren Buffett's company Berkshire Hathaway owns several stocks with strong dividends.  Dividend stocks can be nice to own because they often provide reliable, passive income, even during volatile markets.  Warren Buffett and his company, Berkshire Hathaway, have never paid a dividend, primarily because Buffett has always believed that he could deploy capital in a more rewarding manner for shareholders.
